<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1105,1440]" pageId="8" pageNumber="52">Putative synapomorphies:—basal leaves 1–2, probably flattened in transverse section; tunic leathery, dark grey to dark brown; inflorescence umbellate; filament glabrous; tepals acute at the apex, yellow adaxially, hardened and enlarged after anthesis.</paragraph>
